The following is a description, by way of example only and with reference to the accompanying drawings, of presently preferred embodiments of the invention. In the drawings:-
Figure 1 is a schematic top view of a prior art furnace utilizing air-fuel combustion with oxy-fuel combustion boosting at the hot spot position;
Figure 2 is a schematic top view of a prior art furnace utilizing air-fuel combustion with oxy-fuel combustion boosting at the zero port position;
Figure 3 is a schematic top view of a prior art furnace utilizing only oxy-fuel combustion;
Figure 4 is a schematic top plan view of a first embodiment of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 5 is a schematic top plan view of a second embodiment of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 6 is a schematic top plan view of a third embodiment of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 7 is a schematic top plan view of a fourth embodiment of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 8 is a schematic top plan view of a fifth embodiment of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 9 is a cross-sectional view illustrating a technique for protecting the crown or roof of the furnace of the present invention;
Figure 10 is a cross-sectional view illustrating the use of oxygen staged combustion in a furnace of the present invention;
Figure 11 is a schematic top plan illustrating oxygen enrichment of the combustion air in the Figure 6 embodiment of the furnace of the present invention; and
Figure 12 is a schematic top plan illustrating oxygen lancing of the air-fuel flame in the Figure 6 embodiment of the furnace of the present invention.

